Author:  BURTON
Vol / Page:  3
Edition:
Quote:  On a permanent marae, hangis were dug out of the floor of a cookhouse (<i>kauta</i>), which was usually a simple lean-to shelter but might be a sturdily constructed house (<i>whare umu</i>) with shuttered windows and outlets for smoke.
